Analysis of the Target Model
• Total Blocks & Layers  
  The model uses six total blocks arranged in three “layers” top‐to‐bottom:  
  1) A single yellow block on top  
  2) A middle layer made of two red halves forming the circular “tunnel” in the center and one tall green block on each side  
  3) A single yellow block on the bottom  

• Spatial Relationships  
  – The circular red center is actually two red half‐cylinder pieces joined to make the ring.  
  – Each green block stands vertically on the left and right, flush against the red ring halves.  
  – One thin yellow rectangle sits on top of all four middle pieces; one identical yellow rectangle forms the bottom layer.  

Selecting the Correct Dictionary Blocks

1) Red Ring Halves: Use block #6 (left half) plus block #5 (right half). Placed together, they form the round opening.  
2) Green Sides: Use block #9 on the left and block #10 on the right (both are tall green rectangles oriented exactly as shown).  
3) Top and Bottom Yellow “Slabs”: Use block #13 for the top and block #14 for the bottom (both are thin yellow rectangles oriented horizontally as in the dictionary).  

Assembly Order

{  
  Step1: Move block with index 14  // place yellow bottom  
  Step2: Move block with index 9   // left green block  
  Step3: Move block with index 10  // right green block  
  Step4: Move block with index 6   // left half of red ring  
  Step5: Move block with index 5   // right half of red ring  
  Step6: Move block with index 13  // place yellow top  
}
